`400 Bad Request` usually indicates `invalid or malformed` request or when content-type is  wrong .

 - please make sure two main headers Authorization and `Content-Type` 
   are defined which are necessary along with other headers.
 - Make sure content type is set that has the form your data has i.e.;
   It should reflect the content type of your data.
 - For example, if your content body is XML , Content-Type should be set
   with &#39;application/xml&#39;, for JSON, “application/json &#39;&#39;, etc.. If
   content is plain text, simply set &#39;text/plain&#39; or multipart/form-data
   with boundary

*Examples:*


&gt;     
&gt;     1. conn.setRequestProperty(&quot;Content-Type&quot;,&quot;application/json&quot;)
&gt;     2. conn.setRequestProperty(&quot;Content-Type&quot;, &quot;application/x-www-form-urlencoded&quot;);
&gt;     3. conn.setRequestProperty(&quot;Content-type&quot;, &quot;application/octet-stream&quot;);
&gt;     4. conn.setRequestProperty(&quot;Accept&quot;, &quot;application/xml&quot;);
&gt;     5. conn.setRequestProperty(&quot;Accept&quot;, &quot;text/html, text/plain,application/json,application/xhtml+xml,application/xml;q=0.9,*/*;q=0.8&quot;);

Also check if content size declaration can be given according to file size.

